        <h1>What is Expected During a Zoom Session</h1>
        <strong>All students must:</strong>

        <ul>
            <li>Be in a well-lit area with the light source in front of you and a simple background.</li>
            <li>Avoid sitting in front of a window or light source, it causes glare and shadows.</li>
            <li>Wear solid colors that contrast with your skin. No patterns or busy designs.</li>
            <li>Your video must be stabilized – be sure your device is on a stable, non-moving surface.</li>
            <li>Signing Space – ensure your screen is tall enough to view from your waist up to the top of your head and
                wide enough to see outstretched elbows on either side.</li>
        </ul>
        <span class="text-info">Important Note:</span> It is the student’s responsibility to ensure that their computer
        and internet connection are working before each session. Technical issues and unclear video could result in a
        canceled lesson.
        <br />
